Melee (soulflame horn)=

Even though Kree'arra has extremely high melee defences, the special attack of the [[soulflame horn]] can be used to make the player's next melee hit always land. Since the horn's special attack only works if another player is near the user, it is mandatory to kill Kree'arra in a small team with this method, with duos and trios working the best. Additionally, the player must be using a halberd since Kree'arra is airborne; the [[noxious halberd]] is the only viable halberd for this method.
<br/>
All players should stand under Kree'arra after every attack, and use the soulflame horn's special attack while under him. While it is possible for a team to use only one soulflame horn and simply trade the horn between players after killing the minions, it is recommended for all players to have a soulflame horn in the event the player currently using the horn uses all of their special attacks (and thus guaranteed hits for the party) before Kree'arra is dead.
<br/>
Despite melee armour giving high ranged defence bonuses, it is still recommended to pray Protect from Missiles to avoid potentially getting comboed by Kree'arra. Switch to Protect from Magic after Kree'arra dies to kill the magic minion.

